    • Method Detail

      • execute

        public T execute(Arguments<T> arguments)

        Applies the operations function to the argument(s) given.

        If the number of arguments given does not match the operations arity, then an exception will be thrown.

        Parameters:
        arguments - A collection of arguments (should be at most 1).
        Throws:
        - When the number of arguments does not match the arity.
